 According to Moeti Mmusi of the Provincial Safety, Security and Liaison, five of the nine deceased are from Badplaas, Hendrina and Carolina.
The other four are reportedly from Limpopo, KwaZulu-Natal, and the North West provinces. Mr Mmusi also added that the DNA samples will be conducted on family members to determine whether their DNA matches the deceased’s on July 16. The Executive Mayor of the Steve Tshwete Local Municipality, Bajudi Tolo also sent his condolence to the families. “It is unfortunate that the road has to claim breadwinners. We urge motorists to be cautious when driving” •On Friday a mini-bus collided with a truck on the N11 between Middelburg and Hendrina. Nine of the people in the taxi burnt to death while the drivers of the truck and taxi were rushed to the hospital for medical treatment.     The ferals need help #TrafficAlert: R555 closed, seven die in horrific crash Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 